fields.title: 15 questions for the smartest man in tech
fields.wf_description: Q&A style
fields.wf_content: As a boy, Tony was fascinated with building and controlling machines. At the age of 15 Tony entered the undergraduate electrical engineering program at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), and graduated with two master’s degrees by age 19.

fields.excerpt: Tony Stark is super smart
fields.title: 27 Questions for the Smartest Man in Tech
fields.wf_description: Q&A
fields.wf_content: Tony went to work for Stark Industries, but showed more interest in living a reckless playboy lifestyle than using his engineering skills. At the age of 21, Tony inherited Stark Enterprises when his parents were killed in a car accident secretly orchestrated by rival corporation Republic Oil (later ROXXON). Still lacking in business acumen, Tony promoted secretary Virginia "Pepper" Potts to be his executive assistant and left the majority of his workload on her so that he could avoid what he saw as a burden.

fields.excerpt: All the answers
fields.title: We've got questions for TS and he's got answers
fields.wf_description: Q&A
fields.wf_content: Renaming his corporation Stark International, Tony resolved to abandon munitions production in favor of electronics and computer engineering after witnessing firsthand the impact his company’s weapons had on innocent lives.

fields.excerpt: Stark has left weapons of war behind in favor of building tech for peace
fields.title: Man of war or hero for a new age?
fields.wf_description: Q&A
fields.wf_content: At first, Tony found his new life a torment; his armor’s chest plate had to be worn constantly and required frequent recharging. He kept the armor a secret from everyone, including his fiancée, Joanna Nivena. Turning suicidal and drinking heavily, Tony was supported by Joanna, with whom he shared his secret identity. Joanna encouraged him to use his armor as a super hero, but ultimately called off the engagement knowing Tony would not be the family man she desired.

fields.title: A higher form of war.

fields.title: Is Tony Stark the hero we need?
fields.wf_description: Q & A web profile of Tony Stark
fields.wf_content:
At the age of 15 Tony entered the undergraduate electrical engineering program at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), and graduated with two master’s degrees by age 19. Tony went to work for Stark Industries, but showed more interest in living a reckless playboy lifestyle than using his engineering skills. At the age of 21, Tony inherited Stark Enterprises when his parents were killed in a car accident secretly orchestrated by rival corporation ROXXON.

Renaming his corporation Stark International, Tony resolved to abandon munitions production in favor of electronics and computer engineering after witnessing firsthand the impact his company’s weapons had on innocent lives.

Despite seeming to have everything a man could want, Tony was under much stress. The machinations of rival industrialist Justin Hammer and SHIELD’s constant pressure drove Tony further into drinking. His girlfriend at the time, Bethany Kabe, kept Tony from continued succumbing to his alcoholism. Their relationship ended when Bethany’s presumed-dead husband was discovered alive.

fields.excerpt: Following the deaths of several mayors and mayoral candidates, including his own mother, Oliver Queen is running for office.
fields.captions: Photo 1: Oliver's campaign is being managed by his younger sister, Thea.
fields.title: Oliver Queen is running for Mayor
fields.wf_description: Web profile of queen's campaign, includes video embed of interview.
fields.wf_content:
Star City is no stranger to the troubled, and frequently illegal, antics of Oliver Queen. Queen spent much of his youth a billionaire's heir embibing in the excesses of his family's life. Then came the boat accident that claimed the life of Robert Queen and left Oliver stranded on a desserted island for five years. An older, quieter Oliver shocked the world by turning up alive five years later.

His mother, Moira, ran for the office of mayor last year before being murdered. Now Oliver is looking at the same office, supported by his sister.

fields.title: Is Tony Stark the hero we need?
fields.excerpt: Tony Stark might be the smartest man in tech.
fields.wf_description: Q & A web profile of Tony Stark
fields.wf_content:
At the age of 15 Tony entered the undergraduate electrical engineering program at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), and graduated with two master’s degrees by age 19. Tony went to work for Stark Industries, but showed more interest in living a reckless playboy lifestyle than using his engineering skills. At the age of 21, Tony inherited Stark Enterprises when his parents were killed in a car accident secretly orchestrated by rival corporation ROXXON.

Renaming his corporation Stark International, Tony resolved to abandon munitions production in favor of electronics and computer engineering after witnessing firsthand the impact his company’s weapons had on innocent lives.

Despite seeming to have everything a man could want, Tony was under much stress. The machinations of rival industrialist Justin Hammer and SHIELD’s constant pressure drove Tony further into drinking. His girlfriend at the time, Bethany Kabe, kept Tony from continued succumbing to his alcoholism. Their relationship ended when Bethany’s presumed-dead husband was discovered alive.

fields.excerpt: What does the emergence of Ultron mean for the world?
fields.vf_description: Video piece examining what happened with Ultron.
fields.title: A Suit of Armor Around the World
fields.vf_content:
Ultron: Stark asked for a savior, and settled for a slave.
The Vision: I suppose we're both disappointments.
Ultron: [laughs] I suppose we are.
The Vision: Humans are odd. They think order and chaos are somehow opposites and try to control what can't be. But there is grace in their failings. I think you missed that.
Ultron: They're doomed!
The Vision: Yes... but a thing isn't beautiful because it lasts. It is a privilege to be among them.
Ultron: You're unbelievably naïve.
The Vision: Well, I was born yesterday.
